<HEADLINE>
FT  04 NOV 92 / British Steel ponders longer holidays
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITISH STEEL is considering extending Christmas holidays in its strip
division to reduce production.
It could not say how many workers faced short-time working and extended
Christmas holidays. Market conditions were 'changing all the time' and not
all workers were likely to be affected in the same way.
The corporation said that it would not rule out redundancies although it
emphasised that no final decision had been taken.
It would not to disclose how many of its 3,000 workers at the Llanwern strip
production plant were working 15 shifts a week rather than the usual 21.
</TEXT>
