<HEADLINE>
FT  04 NOV 92 / International Company News: General Mills to end Nabisco
deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MINNEAPOLIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
GENERAL Mills, the Minnesota-based foods company, said it and Nabisco, a
unit of RJR Nabisco Holdings, had mutually agreed to terminate a contract
signed on September 1 for General Mills to buy Nabisco's US and Canadian
ready-to-eat cold cereal business, Reuter reports from Minneapolis.
The companies said the prospect of a lengthy and prolonged review by federal
and state regulatory authorities, which now appeared likely, would preclude
completion of the transaction within a reasonable period of time.
General Mills agreed to purchase the ready-to-eat cereals business of RJR
Nabisco for Dollars 450m cash.
