FT  03 NOV 92 / Letter: Reject the impassioned lobbies
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr DAVID STARKIE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Your leader, 'One cheer for the chancellor' (October 30), affirms the
chancellor's right to insist on the maintenance of economically valuable
capital spending in a recession. However, not all capital projects currently
vying for support fall into this category. One notable example is London's
Jubilee line, which has a negative return measured on a cost benefit basis.
The credibility of the government's economic policy is to be judged by its
willingness to reject such cases despite impassioned lobbying.
David Starkie,
Garden Cottage,
Benham Park,
Newbury, Berks RG16 8LX
</TEXT>
