FT  03 NOV 92 / Letter: An hourly rate to make an electronics engineer happy
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr FRED SANDER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, I am obliged to Mr John Richards for his enlightenment as to the
enormous cost of bank cashiers (Letters, October 31). As an experiment I
switched on a timer unit and asked my wife to hand me a Pounds 10 note over
my desk. I opened a desk drawer, counted out Pounds 10 in coins and handed
them to her.
This operation took 15 seconds; so allow five seconds wasted time per
transaction and at current bank charges this works out at Pounds 360 an
hour.
As a humble 66-year-old electronics engineer I would be more than happy to
give change all day at this rate of income.
Fred Sander,
Gainsborough House,
153 Liverpool Road South,
Maghull,
Merseyside L31 8AA
</TEXT>
