FT  03 NOV 92 / Management (The Growing Business): VAT inspectors rake in a
record - In a Nutshell
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Value added tax inspectors made fewer visits to businesses in 1991-92 but
collected more tax.
The number of visits fell from 440,000 to 426,000 in the year ended March
31, 1992 but additional tax collected rose from Pounds 1.16bn to a record
Pounds 1.46bn, according to the annual report of Customs &amp; Excise.
An extra Pounds 27m was collected in the form of serious misdeclaration
penalties while Pounds 43m was levied in default interest charges.
