<TEXT>
THE TURKISH Government is offering to sell its 20 per cent share in Netas,
the local subsidiary of Northern Telecom of Canada, plus stakes in four
other companies in an attempt to revive its flagging privatisation
programme.
The five companies are expected to raise TL641bn (Dollars 85.3m). Bids have
to be submitted by December 1.
The Public Participation Administration, which handles the sale of state
assets to the public, plans to make sales worth TL5,500 in 1992, including
the sale of 11 state cement companies. Bids for these are closed.
