A SKr500m (Dollars 86m) agreement that would have given Fyffes, the
Dublin-based fruit and vegetable distributor, 50 per cent of the Swedish
wholesale distributor Saba Trading has collapsed, write Christopher
Brown-Humes in Stockholm and Tim Coone in Dublin.
