<HEADLINE>
FT  03 NOV 92 / UK Company News: British Assets value declines
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Over the 12 months to September 30 net asset value at British Assets Trust,
which has an international portfolio of over Pounds 500m, fell 5.1 per cent,
from 94.72p to 89.85p.
Earnings per share fell from 4.11p to 4.02p, reflecting a combination of
falling interest rates, a lower value of dollar receipts because of the
declining US exchange rate, and a decrease in dividend payments by quoted UK
companies.
However, the final quarterly dividend is 1.07p to make a total of 4.19p for
the year, against 4.04p. Barring unforeseen circumstances, a minimum
distribution of 4.28p is indicated for the current year.
Investors Capital Trust, 67.5 per cent owned by British Assets, saw net
asset value decline from 116.7p to 111.8p over the year.
Earnings per share worked through at 4.97p (5.12p) and the dividend is
lifted to 5.1p (5.05p) with a final quarterly payment of 1.275p.
</TEXT>
