FT  03 NOV 92 / UK Company News: Stag leaps 21p as bid talks confirmed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Stag Furniture, the Nottingham-based cabinet furniture
manufacturer, yesterday jumped 21p to 96p following rumours, confirmed by
the company, that it was a bid target.
The company said it was in discussions with another party that could lead to
an offer.
In September, Stag announced a 66 per cent fall in first-half pre-tax
profits to Pounds 317,000. The company said margins were under pressure and
the interim dividend was cut from 2.5p to 1.5p.
</TEXT>
