<HEADLINE>
FT  03 NOV 92 / UK Company News: BAe sells communications subsidiaries
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DANIEL GREEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITISH AEROSPACE has dismantled its communications division and sold most
of the parts with the loss of 35 jobs.
The company said the division was 'not part of its core businesses'.
Turnover of the division in 1991 was about Pounds 10m. Only the ground
equipment for the company's Orion communications satellite project will
remain associated with BAe through a joint venture with Kingston
Communications, the telecommunications infrastructure operator for the city
of Hull.
Business Television and Services to Broadcasters, which broadcasts to
specified groups of people, has gone to Maxat.
The Medical Television Network, which provides programmes for doctors to
medical schools was sold to Satellite Information Services, which provides
television pictures to betting shops.
Bishopsgate Systems' data broadcasting goes to Alphameric.
</TEXT>
