FT  03 NOV 92 / Fear of new IRA mainland campaign
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
RUC CHIEF Constable Sir Hugh Annesley yesterday warned of a heightened IRA
terror campaign on the British mainland with more and bigger bombs.
The latest outbreak of violence in London, he said, was only a foretaste of
what might happen. It was clear that militarists now held sway within the
republican movement.
Sir Hugh told the BBC Northern Ireland programme Inside Ulster that lives
had been saved and damage prevented because of interruptions to IRA attacks
in London.
