sway now within the IRA army council,' Sir Hugh said.
He said loyalist paramilitaries in Northern Ireland posed a 'significant
threat' in the Irish Republic.
Meanwhile, the Association of Chief Police Officers defended the present
structure of police ranks, saying the way the structure was used was more
pertinent than any debate about 'losing ranks'.
Its comments were in response to the Sheehy inquiry into police rewards and
duties.
