<HEADLINE>
FT  02 NOV 92 / World News In Brief: Panic faces no-confidence vote
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Milan Panic, the Yugoslav prime minister, may lose a no-confidence vote in
the federal parliament today, after a campaign to discredit him organised by
Slobodan Milosevic, the Serbian president. Page 3. Meanwhile, intense
machine-gun and mortar fire in the Bosnian capital Sarajevo accompanied the
start of the UN-brokered 'Week of Tranquillity' for the former Yugoslavia.
</TEXT>
